The forces of the giant strike are gathering
The League Unions and the National Federation of Workers' Commissions will constitute a strike commission on Friday to coordinate the Monday strike that will last indefinitely.
On Saturday a protest rally will be held, while on Monday - the day on which the final vote on the public health law will be held - the work stoppage will begin.
Surely this action will cause great difficulties in the transport, since the railway traffic will be stopped completely and until 1 pm the workers of the Collective Transport Company of Budapest will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon the League Trade Unions will report on the details of their Monday strike they will hold together with the National Federation of Workers' Commissions.
The strike commission of LIGA and the National Trade Union of Machinists will also be set up to coordinate Monday's actions.
On Saturday a protest rally will be held, while on Monday the participating unions will strike indefinitely, if no agreement is reached with the government.
This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report on the date of the end of the strike begun.
If the National Assembly disapproves of the public health law, trade unions will immediately withdraw their call for strike.
On the other hand, if the law is passed, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
On the basis of the agenda of Monday of the National Assembly it is also possible that only the public health law will be voted on at very late hours of the night, or perhaps near midnight.
As a result of the strike that will start on Monday, significant difficulties will have to be faced in transport: on the railways it will stop working indefinitely, in the morning part of the collective transport of Budapest and more than half of the intercity bus transport of the Volán companies may be stopped.
At the same time, in many parts of the country, half of the roads will be closed.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the strike, their names are constantly updated on the League's website.
Some unions announced their strike for indefinite time, others for definite time.
Until Thursday afternoon the State Railway and the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) were unable to reach an agreement even on minimum services, although, as Christmas holidays approach, more and more people travel on trains.
According to information received so far, from the beginning of the day until 1 p.m. the workers of the Budapest Collective Transport Company will be on strike, the Budapest Airports from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m., a four-hour strike will be held by the LIGA Trade Unions of the Electrical and Thermal Energy Industry, the Education Unions called for a strike of 2 and the Democratic Union of Educators from 2 to 8 hours.
The Hungarian Association of Physicians will take a national strike at alternative times and the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (SDTSSS) which are part of the Trade Union Cooperation Forum will hold a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands made by the League is that the government withdraw its proposal regarding public health reform and submit a new conception to a social debate.
The second demand is that they gradually introduce the new form of pension calculation that will come into effect next year.
The third is to ensure that, even before 2010, in the case of advanced pensions, it is possible that the occupations that deserve it can enter the system.
The fourth reason for the strike is that the Free Trade Union of Railway Workers (SLTF) which is part of the League Trade Unions, do not accept the proposal of the Ministry of Economy and Transport on the railway side lines and expect another proposal.
Political Capital[b1]: In the country the risk is increased by the Hungarian Guard
According to the Risk Analysis Division (Risk Analysing Division) of the Political Capital, the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed in August of this year with the support of the Movement for a Better Hungary, has increased from several points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region.
In the company's "risk warning" it is written: in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard the greatest political risk is the fact that "with the aggravation of ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Roma population of Hungary, even in the short term violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy is probably the provocation of an event of this nature - added the representative of the research institute.
They affirmed that all this is due to one of the main faults of the protagonists of Hungarian political life: "the protagonists of public life gave the public debate of the gypsy problem to the representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the existing discrepancies between Gypsies and Hungarians".
This aggravates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
In addition, according to the research institute, the activity of the National Guard, as a result of the great attention of the national and international media, "significantly deteriorated the image of Hungary abroad, especially with regard to the stability and democratic development of the country".
They remind us that: from autumn 2006 onwards, the reorganization of the extreme right-wing and radical groups in Hungary received increasing publicity and momentum, and that since summer 2007, numerous organizations have been formed in the country to define themselves as "national self-defence associations".
"The common feature of these groups is that they define themselves as civil organizations, while openly proclaiming the training of their members for defense - even armed - (civil defense, national defense, defense of public order), alluding to the ineptitudes of the police, of the army, that is of the state" - they add.
They said: all this takes place in accordance with the method that tries to give a civil presentation to different political aspirations, based on the discontent of society with politics and with political parties.
For to highlight the civil aspect and the form of association in the case of these associations not only serves to avoid the legal problems of legal registration, but is at the same time a political strategy.
According to the analysis, the activity of the Hungarian Guard is also a risk factor from the point of view of neighbourhood relations.
"In recent months, in many neighboring States they referred to the Hungarian Guard as a potential danger, while the ultra-nationalist political figures of certain neighboring countries, want to justify their own anti-Hungarian policy with the creation of the Hungarian Guard.
All this influences the political stability of the region" - they added.
According to the research institute, the constitution of the Hungarian Guard is not an isolated phenomenon in Central and Eastern Europe, so political risks increased throughout the region.
They wrote that the Hungarian Guard functions in the same way as for example the Bulgarian National Guard, whose constitution was announced in August 2007 by the Bulgarian National Union (UNB) of extreme right.
The constitution of the Bulgarian guard is due to the mass riots of the Gypsies that took place in one of the neighbourhoods of Sofia (Krasna Poliana).
Taking advantage of this situation, the UNB decided to set up the guard, arguing that the organization's objective is "national self-defense."
In his opinion, in the last 17 years there was "Gypsy terror" in Bulgaria, however the state remained powerless and indifferent to the facts - recalls the Political Capital.
They added: this initiative has sparked a lively discussion in Bulgarian public opinion.
As it was written, it indicates the increased risk of ethnic clashes that certain Roma organisations in Bulgaria have announced that in order to resist, they will constitute their own guard.
As the operation of the Hungarian Guard has so far shown similarities with that of the Bulgarian National Guard, it cannot be excluded that also the Hungarian Gypsies react to the threat in a similar way, organizing their own self-defense - it can be read in the warning about the risks of Political Capital.
Attila Juhász, Director of Research for Political Capital, said the news agency's question: Risk analysis is one of the activities of the research institute.
As he said, each year they publish their risk analysis and when they experience something that can influence risk change, they inform the public, as happened in this case, publishing their warning about risks.
The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers in the calendar and has already become a widespread practice that around the holidays - that the coming anus will be less - work days are reorganized.
Even in the EU or North America parties are not uniform.
Hungarian laws make a difference between national holidays, State holidays and holidays.
The festive days are mainly related to religious festivals and historical events.
We celebrate the New Year as well: both the last day of the old year, and the first day of the new year is festive - the latter especially so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written with red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the revolution of 1848 and October 23, a day commemorating the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th we celebrated the founding of the State, on May 1st the feast of work, November 1st and 2nd we remember our deceased family and friends.
In addition, there are two-day feasts in our country: Easter, Pentecost and Christmas.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, so it is often bridged when before or after the party there is only one working day.
In exchange for the weekends so long, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
He is the minister of labor who regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or after the feast.
This legal rule is binding on all employers and their employees, as well as on employees and public officials.
It is not mandatory, however, for companies and service institutions which, because of their role, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the work order can be altered only around the holidays of the end of the year: from the 24th of December practically stops life in the country, since according to experiences, most people "bridge" during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their holidays during these days.
The next year several of our parties will coincide with mid or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working days than this year.
First, the agenda will be changed around the work party so that, for four successive days, workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that Friday, May 2nd will be a festive day.
The other change relates to the feast of October 23rd: on Saturday October 18th, we will have to work instead of Friday 24.
On the other hand, the anus that comes during the holiday of the end of the year will be able to rest, since from 24 December it will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
