Central banks fear that they have the same problems with access to loans and will therefore have to lend more to their customers.
This would reduce consumption and send the American economy into recession with different impacts on the growth of the world economy.
The central banks thus decided, after they did not manage to reduce the so-called LIBOR tariff, London interbank rate that is used for the loan of money in the interbank market.
