What kind of insurance do I have?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of possible accidents, is an important expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of it, among others.
Having the car is just the beginning.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This undertaking is embodied in an insurance contract, which provides that the company receives the value of the premium agreed upon in exchange for liability for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of an accident.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, seniority of the card, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or the use given to it, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so that the more likely they are to suffer an accident, the higher the fee to be paid.
It is for this reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Also, drawing on the accounts, companies have come to the conclusion that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and thus the probability of having some kind of mishap.
By increasing the frequency, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well in order to choose the car insurance that best fits his profile.
We will present here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 find it difficult to hire insurance at an affordable price, such as the low driving experience and seniority of the card.
Although the ideal way to be well insured is insurance at all risks, there are other more economical options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for a free-of-charge risk, so that they get insurance coverage at all risks but at a more feasible price.
Such an agreement would require the customer to pay part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the claim that the customer contributes will be pre-established according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount", specifies Luis Noguera, the highest responsible in Spain of First Europa, online insurance mediator.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against those caused in his own car.
In addition, it would be covered by theft, fire and vehicle loss.
A word of advice.
If you are under the age of 25 try to be careful and avoid casualties as much as possible, as this will impact on the bonus, being able to reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company owns.
On the contrary, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fee.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses," explains Noguera.
After the 25-year-olds, drivers have it easier to hire insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
For this reason, the most recommended thing is to hire a whole risk with franchise.
"Young people are usually unable to make use of the experience they have previously acquired when using an accident, and even when driving," says the director in Spain of the European company, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but still has no children it is preferable that he negotiate insurance at all risk, as long as his financial situation allows him, of course.
For their part, marriages with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be one at all risk with a franchise (this could be 300 euros), or, where a high level of bonus is available, one to third parties extended from the third year of life of the vehicle.
"They carry out a more relaxed driving and have greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchise," Luis Noguera says.
For retirees it is advisable to have insurance at all risk with a franchise (with this being 150 euros), or one to third parties extended when you have a high level of bonus.
It has to be said that car insurance is important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents an important expense, which is why it is essential to properly study the insurance that suits us best according to our personal situation.
