Currently wooden boxes produced in Sweden are like the shadow weighing on Warhol's list of works.
Most of the ninety-four "type" gloss-boxes on this list are fake.
After a few months ago the Swedish newspaper "Expressen" cast doubt on the authenticity of Brillo-Boxes of the year 1968 by Andy Warhol, the Moderna Museet Museum in Stockholm carried out internal research and reached disappointing conclusions: the six "Brillo-Boxes", which the former director of the Pontus Hultén museum gave to the Moderna Museet Museum, are false, and almost a hundred others of "Stockholm type", which are in circulation in the international art market, also result.
Prehistory is too complicated with a confusing relationship between artistic and sponsored productions.
In 1964 Warhol created in New York his first "Brick-Boxes", painted the wooden boxes red, blue and white, with the same sample that had "Brick" soap dust cartons.
According to Warhol, in the 1968 exhibition of his works at the Museum Moderna Musseet were exhibited hundreds of Bright-boxes of cardboard. These were not made by Warhol (because of the expenses), but were brought directly from the cardboard factory of "Brillis".
These were not works of art, but copies (which were only objects) exhibited.
In the same year, 1968, Warhol allowed the production in Sweden of wooden Shine-boxes, but they were not exhibited in the Museum Modern Museet.
Witnesses of those times now speak of almost fifteen boxes, which at that time entered the history of art and auctions as originals of the "Stockhol-type" "Brick-Boxes" authorized by Andy Warhol.
In auctions some of them were bought for more than $100,000.
The problem is that after the famous director of the Pontus Hultén museum made false statements that in 1968 in Sweden were produced and exposed almost one hundred wooden boxes that Warhol left to him.
But in reality, 105 boxes were produced in the same year 1990 in Malmö for Hultén and for the exhibition in St. Petersburg.
At this time Warhol had already died for three years.
Lars Byström, the head of the conservatives of the Museum Moderna Museet, investigated six Brillo-Boxes owned by the museum and also three of the Swedish private property that were manufactured in 1968 in Stockholm. First, their tight silvers were printed and embossed and then painted in oil with the brush.
On the contrary, the structure of the 1990 copies shows that the painting was applied with a roller without directly printing the tight silvers. Moreover, it is not about oil painting, but rather about acrylic painting.
"These boxes have not been authorized by the artist and should be removed from Andy Warhol's official Shine-Box list," says Lars Nittve, the director of the Moderna Museet Museum, adding that if the New York Authentication Commission "Andy Warhol Art" will not reach any conclusion, the Moderna Museet Museum will classify these six boxes as the copies/objects of exhibition."
Already in July the Authentication Commission formally announced that it accepts these "serious accusations" in which these are soap dust boxes.
But from that moment there everything remained in absolute silence.
Rebel soldiers surrender in Manila.
In the Philippines, rebel soldiers who had barricaded themselves in a hotel in Manila and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo have surrendered.
The ringleader Antonio Trillanes, who reproaches the president, corruption and electoral fraud, told a reporter that he could not answer for shedding blood.
Soldiers loyal to the government had raided the hotel using tear gas.
Nearly two hundred soldiers had been barricaded in the building for a few hours.
Almost half of them, including Trillanes, had a Thursday trial for having attempted a coup in 2003 that ended in failure.
He took advantage of the negotiations, so he could suddenly deposit with some 30 sympathizers.
Evidently the military police officers who were to watch him had passed into their ranks and followed their mutiny.
They entered the hotel "Peninsula" and demanded the fall of President Gloria Macapagal Arroyo.
Government troops blocked the neighborhood around the Noble Hotel.
The president called an urgent session of the Security Cabinet.
Norberto Gonzales, the National Security adviser, condemned the behavior of the soldiers.
"People are fed up," Trillanes said.
"We call on people to move into our ranks."
General Danilo Lim, who formerly led the elite Scout Reangers troops, said that the other military troops wanted to follow the march shortly.
Big government critics called a big demonstration against the president on Thursday.
For months his government has been reproached for corruption.
In 2003 the financial district in Manila was a site that attracted all the attention for the mutiny that was attempted against Arroyo.
The uprising failed after about 24 hours because the army wanted to participate.
Since 1986, there have been at least seven coup attempts against the democratically elected government in the Philippines.
United Internet will be Versatel's largest shareholder.
United Internet secured more than 20 percent of the shares of the telecommunication company Versatel.
On Wednesday the company reported that the average price for a share is 14, 46 euros.
You have only 20.05 percent of the share capital.
There were many speculations about the absorption of the company.
There are also options to further increase the financial share at Versatel.
United Internet reported that with this step it wants to accelerate the consolidation of the German DSL market.
On Wednesday they already made assumptions about entering the business, after the Brendenberg bank increased its share of the Duesseldorf network operator by 5 percent to 15.1 percent.
In the financial market that means that the financial institution maintains the equity securities for a third party.
United Internet already in the day before had participated with almost 10 percent to the telecommunication company Drillisch.
Drillisch in the measure of capital increase placed 17,4 million of the new shares that have a value of 106,4 million euros.
The United Internet has purchased 5.15 million shares for 31.4 million euros from them.
In addition, the companies started negotiations on DSL-product marketing cooperations.
"We strengthen our collaboration," the United Internet spokesman explained.
The two companies founded a company together MSP, to acquire the competitor Freenet.
On Thursday the United Internet reported that at the beginning, the two companies want to be happy with the ten percent share of Freenet and do not make use of their right, that is, they involve 18.49 percent of Freenet.
This meant that both companies maintained all options, especially the participation of the public limited liability company Freenet.
Negotiations between United Internet and Freenet on a strategic partnership ended in mid-November.
This "game" with Freenet that will last for many months and is not very understandable is part of the consolidation of the German Telecom market.
By the end of the third quarter Freenet had 2.9 million customers with a mobile phone contract and 1.27 million with a DSL contract or a full contract.
Until now the holding company of United Internet and Drillisch had directly 6.01 percent of the share in Freenet.
Then they had agreed that Drillisch will achieve the other four percent.
The right to buy 18.49 percent of the Vatas investment company was already agreed in August.
